{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Provide a legal pathway to \u201cde-exempt\u201d XL Bully dogs exempted as a precaution",
        "additional_details": "Many of these dogs may not meet the legal \u201ctype\u201d, yet two years later there is still no pathway or reassessment to allow de-exemption.\r\nAs a result, we believe dogs' welfare is unfairly compromised by lifelong restrictions imposed solely because their owners followed Government advice. The Secretary of State and DEFRA must now prioritise establishing a clear and fair de-exemption process.\r\n",
        "background": "In October 2023, DEFRA and the Chief Veterinary Officer advised owners unsure of their dog\u2019s breed type to \u201ctake a precautionary approach\u201d & obtain a certificate of exemption \u201cto be safe.\u201d As ordinary owners are not trained breed assessors, thousands complied in good faith to avoid criminalisation.",
